eless deal in the universal themes that would become a substantial part of his oeuvre: pride, greed, and what makes people behave as they do. Filled with eccentric characters and piercing insights, Powell’s work is achingly hilarious, human, and true.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aPublishers and publishingvFiction. 0aSpiritualismvFiction. 0aTravel writingvFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aart, artist, unsavory, charlatan, crime, criminals, freud, freudian, novels, novelist, social, communication, satire, satirical, comedy, high society, british, britain, wartime, wars, psychoanalysis, film, publishing, sex, cinema, media, technology, relationships, plot, narrative, dialogue, irony, a dance to the music of time, lampoon, publisher, mistaken identity, farce, oeuvre, pride, greed, eccentric, characters, human nature, humanity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226137216423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226137216/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles